1
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:31,520
And now, the great,
the wonderful Mercedes!

2
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:41,000
5,500 tonight.

3
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:44,640
What the hell is she doing?
I'll get her.

4
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,200
Go away!

5
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:19,760
She goes on in a few moments.
Mercedes just began.

6
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,440
You handle it.

7
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:26,400
I can't take any more.
I'm ready to kill her tonight.

8
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,480
A full house tonight, Mr. Baldi.

9
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:36,040
How much have we got?

10
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:38,640
1,250 more than yesterday.

11
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,400
Shall we do something
about the prince's tab?

12
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:45,000
-No discounts. How big is it?
-About 625.

13
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,800
-How many are they?
-Two.

14
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:49,120
Don't charge for the coffee.

15
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:54,000
Mr. Baldi,
I couldn't do a thing.

16
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:56,920
-Insist!
-It's no use.

17
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:59,400
OK, have Mercedes
stay on longer.

18
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,720
Oh, Mr. Baldi, I'll get my bag.

19
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:38,640
I'm sorry to bother you,
but she refuses to get up.

20
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,240
Were you having dinner?

21
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,200
She must be onstage
in 10 minutes...

22
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,680
and she hasn't made up.

23
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,120
Go away!

24
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:54,520
It's me, Zaza. The doctor.

25
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,400
I'm not here.

26
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:14,120
Show yourself, Zaza.

27
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:17,320
Be a good girl and uncover
yourself so I can see you.

28
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:21,200
But I'm a monster.
I'm horrible, Doctor!

29
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:25,160
Zaza, your fans are waiting,
and my dinner is getting cold.

30
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,480
Stop acting
like such a prima donna!

31
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:33,000
Doctor, I'm so unhappy,
so unhappy. If you only knew!

32
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:35,400
You're a little depressed.
It'll pass.

33
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:38,920
I want to die, Doctor.
I want to die!

34
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:41,680
Were you having dinner?
Can it be reheated?

35
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,600
Rabbit cacciatore.

36
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:45,080
That reheats well.

37
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:49,920
Here's what you do.
Put it in a double boiler.

38
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:53,120
But, attention, it has to be
a double boiler.

39
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:57,160
I always tell my friends,
the secret is the double boiler.

40
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,480
Are you dying or cooking?

41
00:05:58,480 --> 00:06:01,160
Look who's talking!
It's your fault I'm like this.

42
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:05,160
Look what I have become.
A human larva. A dried up fig!

43
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,880
A dried up fig.

44
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:10,280
Before meeting you,
I had a firm, soft skin.

45
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,680
Look what a horror I am now.

46
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:15,720
Every night the same thing.
I taped it yesterday.

47
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,800
I suffer, and he plays.

48
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:19,560
Shall I play it back?

49
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,680
I'll give him a shot.

50
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,680
No, Doctor! No shots!

51
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,680
Ask his understudy
to replace him.

52
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,560
I'll behave.

53
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:29,360
Well...

54
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:34,080
Then, are we going to work?

55
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,920
Any tranquilizers left?

56
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:38,320
There are a few left in the box.

57
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,040
I'm sure.

58
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:48,800
As usual,
two pills after the show.

59
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:51,520
-I'm leaving.
-Good-bye, Doctor.

60
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,800
The season's just begun.

61
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:59,000
If he gets sick,
do I close the club?

62
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:01,880
It's nothing serious.
He's just overtired.

63
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:05,720
Be kind to him,
and everything will be fine.

64
00:07:05,760 --> 00:07:08,560
-Good night, Mr. Baldi.
-Good night, and thanks again.

65
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,920
Do you know what time it is?

66
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,040
You want to ruin the business?

67
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:44,480
You're doing it on purpose.

68
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:50,160
Why do you put makeup
on your legs?

69
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:52,920
Nobody sees your legs on stage.

70
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:00,880
Indifference is
the most awful thing, Renato.

71
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:06,520
I've been dieting for two months
and you haven't even noticed...

72
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:08,440
that I've lost weight.

73
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:13,440
I've ruined my health for you...

74
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,560
with those diet pills
and diuretics.

75
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:18,280
And nothing from you...
not a word.

76
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:20,080
No support.

77
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:24,240
You don't notice me anymore.
You don't love me anymore.

78
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:27,120
Just the other day...

79
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:29,880
I bought a delightful outfit.

80
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:33,200
I put it on.
Just to please you.

81
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:35,400
Nothing.

82
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:39,080
I'll wind up in a nut house
if you continue.

83
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,680
Everything's possible.

84
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:45,600
You don't love me anymore.

85
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:49,120
After so many years, you think
of me as a bowl of minestrone...

86
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:51,160
not as the queen of the stage.

87
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,360
You're being unfaithful.

88
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:57,000
Here we go again!

89
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:59,560
There's a man in your life.

90
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,280
There aren't any men.

91
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:05,160
Just 250 people waiting
for the leading lady...

92
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:07,160
to make up her mind.

93
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:21,560
They pay a lot to see you...
to applaud you...

94
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:24,040
to applaud
the great Zaza Napoli!

95
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,440
And what do you do
while I'm onstage?

96
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:31,760
Where do you go while
I'm killing myself onstage?

97
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:38,360
Go ahead. Hit me.

98
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,480
Hit me.

99
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,200
Well, how is it?

100
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:56,880
It'll be fine. Don't worry,
darling. You can't even see it.

101
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:59,320
Did you hurt yourself
with your fists?

102
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,520
Darling, then you still love me?

103
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,240
Of course. Hurry up.

104
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,840
What's wrong?

105
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,720
-My fan.
-Jacob will bring it to you.

106
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:15,520
-I can't sing without my fan!
-Jacob, get Zaza's fan!

107
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,080
My fan!

108
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:23,600
Good evening, sweetheart.

109
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:35,080
Bravo, Mercedes. You've already
sung too much. Go, go.

110
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,520
Go on. Don't just stand here.

111
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:39,240
Announce Albin.

112
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:42,040
Enough of those chocolates.
Enough!

113
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,840
Renato, I've had enough
of your beautiful lady!

114
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:57,440
Don't shout
when a colleague is working.

115
00:10:57,480 --> 00:11:01,680
-I could have finished myself.
-Go to hell!

116
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,760
What am I being paid for?

117
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,240
-To sing 4 songs or 8?
-To sing 16!

118
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:09,400
I can't depend on Madam's moods.

119
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,480
She only cares about
being in bed with you.

120
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:15,000
How dare you! As of tomorrow,
you dress like a man!

121
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:18,840
-Not like a man! Forgive me!
-What is said is said. Henry.

122
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:24,200
-So where's that stupid fan?
-Coming.

123
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:33,360
Jacob!

124
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:36,840
I told you not to prance
about the house naked.

125
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:40,160
You don't like it? Why don't
you let me dance? Look at me.

126
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:42,920
What do the others have
that I don't?

127
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:46,360
You have something more,
even if it's of no use to you.

128
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:49,240
Go get dressed.
And take the evening off.

129
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,720
That way,
I won't have you underfoot.

130
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,440
I don't believe this.

131
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:59,760
Can I talk to you for a moment?

132
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:03,280
It's late, Petunia,
and I have an appointment.

133
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:13,320
What's the matter?

134
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,360
What's the matter?

135
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:23,920
-What have you done this time?
-I'm expecting a baby.

136
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,320
I'm expecting a baby.

137
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:30,240
You got your wife pregnant?

138
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,440
But it's the seventh one.

139
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:39,560
How do you expect
to have a career?

140
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:43,400
Look at yourself in the mirror.

141
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:47,920
Procreation is wearing you out.
You're looking older day by day.

142
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,200
It's true.

143
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:52,160
OK, I'll have
the administration...

144
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:54,840
compensate you
for this misfortune.

145
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,760
That's fine. Go back to work.

146
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,000
I'll be forever grateful.

147
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,880
And give up this fixation.

148
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:34,240
Take that off your head, or I'll
tell Albin you wear his wigs.

149
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:37,440
And I'll tell him you have
romantic dinners while he works.

150
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:39,480
Get out of here, you idiot!

151
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:38,280
More handsome than ever.

152
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:45,480
How about a drink?

153
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:55,920
Is Zaza onstage?

154
00:14:55,960 --> 00:15:00,040
For two more hours.
So we won't be disturbed.

155
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:05,120
I gave Jacob the night off.
We're all alone.

156
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,480
You look good.

157
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:28,200
I'm all bloated. Work.

158
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:31,320
I work too much,
I get upset, and I bloat.

159
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:37,320
-You think I look good?
-Dazzling!

160
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,040
You're really sweet.

161
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:43,120
Yes, my body is
still good, actually.

162
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,400
I have something to tell you.

163
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,080
This isn't easy.

164
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:58,760
I'm getting married.

165
00:16:05,920 --> 00:16:07,960
I was going to write you,
but a letter...

166
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,840
She's a great girl.
You'll see.

167
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,440
You upset?

168
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,120
On the contrary,
I should be happy.

169
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:29,680
I always hoped you'd
fall in love with a girl...

170
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,240
so I should be happy.

171
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,400
No, everything's fine.

172
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:40,840
I raise a boy
for 20 years...my son.

173
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:44,240
Then a girl comes
and steals him.

174
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,160
A whore.

175
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,960
A whore. Yes, a whore.

176
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,640
Listen carefully.

177
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:05,320
If you marry her,
never set foot in here again.

178
00:17:05,360 --> 00:17:08,520
I won't give you another cent.
Choose.

179
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:11,480
Good-bye, Dad.

180
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:16,600
You little idiot, come here.

181
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:20,320
Let's have a toast
for this catastrophe.

182
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:22,600
Did you think I'd fall for that?

183
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:25,560
No, but it was worth a try.

184
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,720
Come on. Let's toast.

185
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:31,600
You always toast a wedding.
To the bride and groom !

186
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:37,360
-What's the whore's name?
-Please, Dad.

187
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,880
Sorry. What's the girl's name?

188
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:59,840
So, you've been seeing a boy
in Paris for a year...

189
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,320
and we only find out now.

190
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,040
Answer.

191
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:06,200
Answer me!

192
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:08,440
You're scaring her, Simon.

193
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,520
She'll never talk
if you go on that way.

194
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:17,760
He's a nice boy, Father.
And very serious.

195
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,120
He was the one
to mention marriage.

196
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,480
What do his parents do?

197
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:31,960
What do his parents do?!

198
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:44,360
Hold on. It's for you.

199
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:58,280
I spoke to him. And you?

200
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:01,440
I spoke to mine, too.
He's happy.

201
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:02,920
Whore!

202
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:05,560
He opened champagne
to celebrate the news.

203
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,480
I've got the glass in my hand.

204
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,480
To our love, Andrea.

205
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:14,080
I'll put him on.

206
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:18,560
No.

207
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:21,800
Hello?

208
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:23,400
To your happiness,
Andrea.

209
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,120
Shit!

210
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:29,400
No, not you.
I just broke the glass.

211
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:31,880
My best wishes
for your happiness.

212
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:32,840
Here.

213
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:35,840
Whore.

214
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:38,800
Your father's nice.

215
00:19:38,840 --> 00:19:41,680
Listen,
I'm with my parents.

216
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:43,760
Can I call you
tomorrow morning?

217
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:46,000
No, no, don't worry.

218
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,920
I do, too.
Until tomorrow.

219
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:54,440
Everything went fine...
thank goodness.

220
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:58,440
Did you hear how clear
their voices were?

221
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:01,440
Like they were
next door.

222
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:04,040
It was really clear.

223
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,080
Well, l...

224
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:11,840
It's late.
I'm going to bed.

225
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:16,040
Andrea, we asked you
what the young man's parents do.

226
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:17,840
His parents?

227
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:20,280
Nothing.

228
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:23,600
Well, they're vacationing
on the Cote d'Azur.

229
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:27,280
Yes...but they're not
on vacation all the time.

230
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:30,840
So what does his father do?

231
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,800
His father...

232
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:35,400
He's in the arts,
I think.

233
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:41,640
Cultural affairs,
in fact.

234
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:43,120
He's a Cultural Attaché.

235
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:46,280
That's it...
at the Italian Embassy.

236
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:50,080
Oh, good.
He's a diplomat.

237
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:51,720
Diplomats. Important people!

238
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:54,320
Why didn't you tell us
right away?

239
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,480
Does his mother work?

240
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:02,880
No, his mother takes care of
the children.

241
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,240
She has lots of them.

242
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:11,640
Good morning.
The little one's arrived.

243
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:14,560
-How about a nice roast?
-Fine. I'll pick it up later.

244
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:18,800
I want some pasta
and some Parmesan.

245
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:22,160
-The boy's home?
-Yes, and I've got to hurry.

246
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:25,680
Good morning.
The usual?

247
00:21:25,720 --> 00:21:27,600
Yes, a cake with
the inscription...

248
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,400
"To my Lolo, from Auntie."

249
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:33,960
I've got to run.
He'll be waking up any minute.

250
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,560
Shall I deliver the cake?

251
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,160
No. Jacob'll pick it up.

252
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,120
I'm taking a chocolate.

253
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:41,800
Jacob!

254
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:47,480
Who did I see?

255
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:50,800
Who did I see there?
Who arrived?

256
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,240
The little white man.

257
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:03,280
This coffee really stinks.

258
00:22:03,320 --> 00:22:06,160
You French make shitty coffee.

259
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:09,520
I've been called black,
I've been called queer...

