00:38:11,120 --> 00:38:13,480
What will I tell him?

523
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:18,560
"Get out, you're in the way.
Get out, fag."

524
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:20,640
You could find
a nicer way.

525
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:40,000
Everything OK?

526
00:38:40,040 --> 00:38:40,960
Just fine.

527
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:45,000
You shouldn't be out
in the sun.

528
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:47,400
A suntan is becoming.

529
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:52,480
I know,
but in your condition...

530
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:54,800
the sun isn't good.

531
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:58,720
Why do you say that?

532
00:38:58,760 --> 00:39:00,640
Did you look in
the mirror today?

533
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:04,160
-What's the matter with me?
-You're green.

534
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:06,640
Suntanned.

535
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:08,840
Yes, suntan green.

536
00:39:11,240 --> 00:39:12,640
I'm a little worried.

537
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:18,400
I think you really
need a vacation.

538
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:22,000
But why should I take
a vacation? I feel great.

539
00:39:23,240 --> 00:39:24,520
OK, forget
I mentioned it.

540
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:34,200
Renato, are you saying this
to scare me?

541
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:36,440
You know something.

542
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:39,560
The doctor told you
something.

543
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:42,520
No. The doctor
didn't tell me a thing.

544
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:48,080
No, I'm the one who thinks
that since you're so nervous...

545
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:49,520
and rundown...

546
00:39:49,560 --> 00:39:52,760
a few days off wouldn't
do you any harm.

547
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:07,120
Listen, Renato, when you
begin to talk like this...

548
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:08,600
it's because you want
to tell me something.

549
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:11,400
Don't try to fool me.

550
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:15,240
I'm not 15 anymore.
I know certain tricks.

551
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:20,240
And this, Renato,
isn't nice.

552
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:23,320
It's not worthy of you.

553
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:28,640
You know what day it is?

554
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:31,880
June the 25th.

555
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:35,720
As you say.

556
00:40:37,040 --> 00:40:38,440
Our anniversary.

557
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:41,480
20 years
of living together.

558
00:40:43,120 --> 00:40:45,320
20 happy years.

559
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:47,720
And you choose today
to lie to me...

560
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:50,120
in the most despicable way.

561
00:40:50,160 --> 00:40:51,240
And to try to deceive me.

562
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:54,920
Do you love Laurent?

563
00:40:56,080 --> 00:40:57,160
Why do you ask me this?

564
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:03,080
If you love Laurent,
you'll go.

565
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:17,800
The little
white master called?

566
00:41:17,840 --> 00:41:19,400
Cut it out and get rid
of the discus thrower.

567
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:23,720
Hurry.
There's not much time.

568
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:28,600
I'm being exiled,
rejected like a leper!

569
00:41:28,640 --> 00:41:30,200
You're ashamed of me!

570
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:32,760
I've watched over
that boy.

571
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:34,360
I've sacrificed myself
for him.

572
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:36,920
I've been a mother to him
for 20 years.

573
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:38,480
Albin, listen.

574
00:41:38,520 --> 00:41:41,560
No!
You listen to me, Renato!

575
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:44,760
Either I stay here
to receive the in-laws...

576
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:46,720
or I'll never set foot
in here again!

577
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:50,720
What's the matter?

578
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:55,720
Laurent, I told you
to wait a while.

579
00:41:59,200 --> 00:42:02,400
It's nothing.
I've understood.

580
00:42:10,400 --> 00:42:12,920
I'm being excluded.

581
00:42:12,960 --> 00:42:15,040
I'm being thrown out
of my own house.

582
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:19,040
It doesn't matter.
I'm leaving.

583
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:21,400
I'll leave you.

584
00:42:21,440 --> 00:42:24,560
The monster.
The monster is leaving.

585
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:37,160
Are you happy now?

586
00:42:51,440 --> 00:42:52,400
Come in.

587
00:42:57,040 --> 00:42:58,320
Come back in.

588
00:43:01,360 --> 00:43:02,960
Come cry at home.

589
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:09,160
Albin,
stop acting like a fool!

590
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:12,080
I don't want to see you anymore.
You've ruined everything.

591
00:43:12,080 --> 00:43:14,640
OK, you win.
You can stay.

592
00:43:16,240 --> 00:43:18,920
I can't take any more.
My heart, Renato.

593
00:43:18,960 --> 00:43:20,080
I'm not that young.

594
00:43:20,120 --> 00:43:21,760
All these emotions...
it's too much.

595
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:25,320
Feel my pulse.
Oh, God, I'm collapsing.

596
00:43:26,120 --> 00:43:27,520
Come, we'll go
to the bar.

597
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:30,280
It's the end.
The end.

598
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:42,720
You're weak. You haven't
eaten for hours.

599
00:43:50,440 --> 00:43:52,320
No, no,
he's just overtired.

600
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:53,600
Do you want
to lie down?

601
00:43:53,640 --> 00:43:55,880
That's OK.
The tea will do.

602
00:43:58,120 --> 00:43:59,880
And some toast.

603
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:04,200
Well, what are we going to do
about tonight?

604
00:44:05,640 --> 00:44:07,200
Quite a problem.

605
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:10,880
Two men like us...
what can we tell them?

606
00:44:10,920 --> 00:44:14,080
Thank you, Darling.
It feels so good.

607
00:44:14,120 --> 00:44:18,200
Well, maybe I could be...
I don't know...a relative.

608
00:44:20,920 --> 00:44:22,200
His uncle, perhaps?

609
00:44:23,480 --> 00:44:25,840
You could say
I'm his uncle.

610
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:29,400
All right,
I can't be his uncle.

611
00:44:30,520 --> 00:44:33,840
In any case, you don't resemble
your character either.

612
00:44:35,160 --> 00:44:37,720
Didn't Laurent say you were
a cultural attaché?

613
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:41,840
Cultural attaché,
like hell, Darling!

614
00:44:41,880 --> 00:44:43,760
You don't know
what culture is!

615
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:46,160
Here it is,
tea and toast.

616
00:44:46,200 --> 00:44:47,160
Feeling better?

617
00:45:01,560 --> 00:45:02,520
I don't know.

618
00:45:08,600 --> 00:45:11,760
Just look how
the great diplomat eats!

619
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:13,560
You're like
a steamroller.

620
00:45:14,520 --> 00:45:16,200
Your pinky.

621
00:45:16,240 --> 00:45:18,760
What's it doing up there?
Just look at it.

622
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:20,840
It does it by itself.

623
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:23,880
You'll say that for
the deputy tonight, huh?

624
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:31,720
Well, let's try to make
a man out of this uncle.

625
00:45:31,760 --> 00:45:33,960
You have to learn
how to hold things.

626
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:37,000
Hold the toast in
a manly way, like this.

627
00:45:37,040 --> 00:45:39,240
Spread the butter
with force.

628
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:42,760
Drink the tea like
a laborer drinks wine.

629
00:45:43,920 --> 00:45:45,160
First,
sit up like a man.

630
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:46,920
What do you want
from me?

631
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:50,240
Please, don't whine
every time I correct you.

632
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:51,240
I'm teaching you.

633
00:45:52,080 --> 00:45:55,720
I want you to look
like a man tonight.

634
00:45:55,760 --> 00:45:58,600
Good, now butter
your toast.

635
00:45:58,640 --> 00:45:59,560
Butter it like a man.

636
00:46:00,240 --> 00:46:02,440
Don't be afraid.
That's the way!

637
00:46:03,600 --> 00:46:05,800
You're doing it
on purpose!

638
00:46:08,240 --> 00:46:09,160
Take another one.

639
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:11,400
I'll never get it.
Never.

640
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:13,480
Don't whine, please,
don't whine!

641
00:46:14,880 --> 00:46:17,560
Now hold this piece
firmly in your hand.

642
00:46:17,600 --> 00:46:22,200
Like a man.
With a strong hand, understand?

643
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:24,760
Like a real man!

644
00:46:24,800 --> 00:46:25,880
Now something
more difficult.

645
00:46:25,920 --> 00:46:26,840
A little jam?

646
00:46:26,880 --> 00:46:27,960
Yes, take the spoon.

647
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:29,720
The teaspoon?

648
00:46:29,760 --> 00:46:31,160
Not like that!

649
00:46:31,200 --> 00:46:35,960
It's not a paintbrush.
It's only a spoon.

650
00:46:36,000 --> 00:46:39,360
Hold it firmly. Boldly.
Understand?

651
00:46:40,960 --> 00:46:42,680
You have something
against me.

652
00:46:42,720 --> 00:46:45,720
You want to kill me,
old bitch!

653
00:46:45,760 --> 00:46:49,080
I'll never get it.
I broke the toast again.

654
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:51,320
It's broken. Too bad.

655
00:46:51,360 --> 00:46:53,400
It's situations
like this...

656
00:46:53,440 --> 00:46:55,960
that force you
to act like a man.

657
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:56,920
Do you understand?

658
00:46:56,960 --> 00:46:59,160
I understand.
You're right.

659
00:46:59,200 --> 00:47:01,400
You have to say
to yourself...

660
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:03,320
"Albin, so you
made a mistake.

661
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:06,040
"It isn't hopeless.
You can try again."

662
00:47:06,080 --> 00:47:07,800
Force yourself.
Take another piece.

663
00:47:07,840 --> 00:47:10,680
You're right.
In the end, it's not serious.

664
00:47:10,720 --> 00:47:14,960
After all,
I still have other ones.

665
00:47:15,920 --> 00:47:17,480
Your pinky...

666
00:47:17,520 --> 00:47:19,360
It does it by itself.

667
00:47:22,320 --> 00:47:24,720
Blow your nose.

668
00:47:24,720 --> 00:47:26,440
Let's go home.

669
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:29,200
Wait.
I need to freshen up.

670
00:47:35,600 --> 00:47:37,040
What have I done now?

671
00:47:37,040 --> 00:47:39,240
What kind of walk
is that?

672
00:47:39,280 --> 00:47:40,200
What's wrong with it?

673
00:47:40,240 --> 00:47:43,080
Walk like that tonight
and we're ruined.

674
00:47:43,120 --> 00:47:44,200
How should I do it?

675
00:47:44,240 --> 00:47:45,800
Come here.

676
00:47:45,840 --> 00:47:47,760
What do you want?

677
00:47:47,760 --> 00:47:49,680
Try to walk
like John Wayne.

678
00:47:50,480 --> 00:47:51,440
The cowboy?

679
00:47:51,440 --> 00:47:55,240
John Wayne gets down
from the horse.

680
00:47:55,280 --> 00:47:59,240
He goes toward the saloon.
He opens the doors, and zap!

681
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:01,200
-Try it.
-I have to be John Wayne?

682
00:48:02,640 --> 00:48:03,920
There I go.

683
00:48:06,960 --> 00:48:08,720
That's John Wayne's daughter!

684
00:48:10,320 --> 00:48:11,760
Look at that fag!

685
00:48:19,760 --> 00:48:21,680
Someone just
called me a fag.

686
00:48:52,080 --> 00:48:54,120
Did you call
my friend a fag?

687
00:49:01,200 --> 00:49:02,920
It's going down.
You can hardly see it.

688
00:49:02,960 --> 00:49:04,400
Relax, darling.

689
00:49:04,400 --> 00:49:07,240
You were wonderful,
marvelous.

690
00:49:08,200 --> 00:49:09,800
I'm proud of you.

691
00:49:10,760 --> 00:49:12,800
That human mountain
looked ridiculous...

692
00:49:12,840 --> 00:49:16,320
when he sat on you and banged
your head on the floor.

693
00:49:16,360 --> 00:49:20,400
I pitied him. A silly brute
who didn't know how to hit you.

694
00:49:22,920 --> 00:49:25,280
No, leave it.
I'll get some ice.

695
00:49:25,320 --> 00:49:26,720
It'll do him good.

696
00:49:26,760 --> 00:49:27,880
Be right back, darling!

697
00:49:35,240 --> 00:49:37,480
I have bad news for you.

698
00:49:37,520 --> 00:49:40,000
I couldn't do it.
I told him to stay tonight.

699
00:49:40,040 --> 00:49:41,120
Why?

700
00:49:41,160 --> 00:49:42,080
What do you mean?

701
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:44,960
Because he nearly
died in my arms.

702
00:49:45,000 --> 00:49:47,040
Because he's been
my companion for years.

703
00:49:47,080 --> 00:49:49,920
And because he has
80% interest in the club.

704
00:49:49,960 --> 00:49:51,560
How are you going
to introduce him?

705
00:49:52,520 --> 00:49:53,440
As your uncle.

706
00:49:53,520 --> 00:49:54,720
Then we're ruined.

707
00:49:54,760 --> 00:49:58,040
Calm down. How stubborn you are.
What a temper!

708
00:49:58,080 --> 00:49:59,720
We can talk it over.

709
00:50:00,840 --> 00:50:04,120
Certainly, it would be ideal
if we had a woman here.

710
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:08,760
Strange, huh? We actually
need a woman here.

711
00:50:12,760 --> 00:50:15,280
Why don't you
call your mother?

712
00:50:15,320 --> 00:50:17,520
-No, never!
-Why?

713
00:50:17,560 --> 00:50:20,640
She abandoned me 20 years ago,
and I won't ask her for a thing!

714
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:23,400
You're not helping
matters much.

715
00:50:23,440 --> 00:50:25,240
OK,
I'll take care of it.

716
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:30,360
I'll take care of it
myself.

717
00:50:33,080 --> 00:50:34,800
You can't be serious.

718
00:50:34,840 --> 00:50:37,000
Go see that witch
after what she did?

719
00:50:37,880 --> 00:50:41,520
-Are you crazy?
-Why?

720
00:51:01,240 --> 00:51:02,920
Mrs. Deblon, please.

721
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:04,840
Ask the secretary
over there.

722
00:51:10,960 --> 00:51:12,000
Come in.

723
00:51:13,200 --> 00:51:14,920
I'd like to see
Mrs. Deblon.

724
00:51:18,160 --> 00:51:19,080
You have an appointment?

725
00:51:19,120 --> 00:51:21,640
No, but tell her
it's Renato Baldi.

726
00:51:21,680 --> 00:51:24,680
I doubt she'll see you
without an appointment.

727
00:51:24,720 --> 00:51:26,600
She's very busy.

728
00:51:26,640 --> 00:51:30,000
At least try.
Tell her Renato Baldi is here.

729
00:51:31,440 --> 00:51:32,520
Wait in the hall.

730
00:51:43,760 --> 00:51:45,160
Madam President
will see you at once.

731
00:51:46,160 --> 00:51:48,680
I'm coming with you.

732
00:51:48,720 --> 00:51:51,240
I won't leave you alone
with that woman.

733
00:51:51,280 --> 00:51:52,440
I know what
she's capable of.

734
00:51:52,480 --> 00:51:54,480
Mrs. Deblon is waiting.

735
00:51:54,520 --> 00:51:56,000
I'm coming.

736
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:58,440
Don't worry.
Everything will be fine.

737
00:52:11,840 --> 00:52:13,520
Renato Baldi.

738
00:52:15,200 --> 00:52:16,480
Dear Madam President.

739
00:52:17,600 --> 00:52:20,000
I must say this is a surprise.

740
00:52:21,280 --> 00:52:22,240
Have a seat.

741
00:52:23,520 --> 00:52:27,480
I never drink in the morning,
but...for the occasion...

742
00:52:27,520 --> 00:52:28,800
What made you come see me?

743
00:52:29,600 --> 00:52:30,560
Laurent.

744
00:52:31,680 --> 00:52:33,320
It's not serious, is it?

745
00:52:33,360 --> 00:52:36,240
He wants to get married.

746
00:52:36,240 --> 00:52:39,320
Already?
How old is he?

747
00:52:39,360 --> 00:52:41,200
You don't even remember.

748
00:52:41,200 --> 00:52:43,520
You haven't seen that boy
for nearly 20 years.

749
00:52:44,480 --> 00:52:47,120
Yes, I know.
Did you come to reproach me?

750
00:52:47,160 --> 00:52:48,760
My goodness, no.

751
00:52:48,800 --> 00:52:51,680
It's just that for the first
time, Laurent needs you.

752
00:53:03,280 --> 00:53:06,760
I can cancel my appointments.
I'll be with you tonight.

753
00:53:06,800 --> 00:53:08,720
-Thank you.
-It's my pleasure.

754
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:12,560
I haven't done much
for that kid in 20 years.

755
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:15,280
-At times, I feel guilty.
-What can I say?

756
00:53:16,240 --> 00:53:18,640
I'm not very maternal.

757
00:53:18,640 --> 00:53:19,600
I am.

758
00:53:21,360 --> 00:53:23,920
It's true.
He's been very lucky.

759
00:53:29,200 --> 00:53:31,440
Well, then...
what time tonight?

760
00:53:31,480 --> 00:53:34,320
At 8:00.
We'll do our little play...

761
00:53:34,320 --> 00:53:36,960
they'll leave,
and everything will be fine.

762
00:53:40,720 --> 00:53:41,840
Do you remember
the revue?

763
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:44,360
How could I forget?

764
00:53:44,400 --> 00:53:45,520
How handsome you were!

765
00:53:47,440 --> 00:53:48,880
I'd never seen
such a body.

766
00:53:49,680 --> 00:53:51,440
Now don't embarrass me.

767
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:57,280
Remember how afraid you were?

768
00:53:57,320 --> 00:53:59,040
I almost had
a heart attack.

769
00:53:59,080 --> 00:54:03,840
I walk in my room
and find a woman in my bed!

770
00:54:03,880 --> 00:54:05,600
I got in by giving
the doorman a tip.

771
00:54:05,640 --> 00:54:07,240
$10 in those days!

772
00:54:07,880 --> 00:54:09,600
I was completely drunk.

773
00:54:09,640 --> 00:54:11,720
And when I saw you in bed nude,
I said to myself...

774
00:54:12,680 --> 00:54:14,240
"Let's try it."

775
00:54:14,280 --> 00:54:17,120
You have to try everything
in life, right?

776
00:54:17,160 --> 00:54:19,240
So much had been
said about it...

777
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:21,960
that I gave in.

778
00:54:24,360 --> 00:54:26,720
How long did
the two of us last?

779
00:54:26,800 --> 00:54:28,800
I can tell you exactly.

780
00:54:28,840 --> 00:54:32,520
From 2:30 to 3:45.
Two times.

781
00:54:45,320 --> 00:54:46,920
It's hot in here.

782
00:54:49,640 --> 00:54:50,920
You haven't changed much.

783
00:54:52,760 --> 00:54:54,360
A few more pounds...

784
00:54:55,320 --> 00:54:56,760
but it's becoming.

785
00:54:58,360 --> 00:55:01,080
It makes you...
more manly.

786
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:05,840
What's all this hair? You
didn't have any when I met you.

787
00:55:05,880 --> 00:55:07,760
I shaved it
for the stage.

788
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:12,400
He shaved it
so I never got to enjoy it.

789
00:55:12,440 --> 00:55:14,040
Careful, Simone.
Careful.

790
00:55:16,440 --> 00:55:18,640
It's a crepe shirt.

791
00:55:18,680 --> 00:55:21,520
With those nails of yours,
you'll...look...

792
00:55:21,560 --> 00:55:23,920
you pulled a thread.

793
00:55:33,080 --> 00:55:34,480
What does that
red light mean?

794
00:55:35,640 --> 00:55:38,760
That Madam President is not
to be disturbed for any reason.

795
00:55:52,560 --> 00:55:53,480
Albin!

796
00:56:04,880 --> 00:56:05,960
Thank you.

797
00:56:07,760 --> 00:56:08,840
Do you have my glasses?

798
00:56:09,840 --> 00:56:10,920
Where are my glasses?

799
00:56:19,320 --> 00:56:21,000
Here it is.

800
00:56:22,160 --> 00:56:25,800
"The death of
President Berthier."

801
00:56:26,640 --> 00:56:28,000
There's nothing at all.

802
00:56:31,920 --> 00:56:34,880
"Exemplary career..."

803
00:56:34,920 --> 00:56:37,000
"Heart attack..."

804
00:56:37,040 --> 00:56:39,880
Nothing here. Excellent.

805
00:56:42,160 --> 00:56:44,480
Nothing here.
It's better this way.

806
00:56:45,600 --> 00:56:48,440
It helps to have friends
who are newspaper editors.

807
00:56:57,680 --> 00:57:00,560
I knew it! I was sure!

808
00:57:00,600 --> 00:57:03,600
Those bastards! Two columns!

809
00:57:03,640 --> 00:57:07,040
"The Happy Death
of President Berthier."

810
00:57:07,080 --> 00:57:08,680
Relax, Simon.

811
00:57:08,720 --> 00:57:10,280
Listen to this.

812
00:57:10,320 --> 00:57:12,920
"The last sentence
uttered by Berthier...

813
00:57:12,960 --> 00:57:16,040
"symbol of the Moral Order,
was, 'Remember my little gift."'

814
00:57:16,080 --> 00:57:19,440
What rats! What rats!
May they die!

815
00:57:19,480 --> 00:57:23,600
Forget this whole story, Simon!
Think of the goal of this trip.

816
00:57:58,360 --> 00:57:59,720
The antique dealer
rented it to me.

817
00:57:59,760 --> 00:58:01,360
He wants it back tomorrow.

818
00:58:04,160 --> 00:58:07,360
I redecorated
the entire living room.

819
00:58:09,480 --> 00:58:11,440
I hope your guests
appreciate it.

820
00:58:14,160 --> 00:58:15,480
What's going on?

821
00:58:27,080 --> 00:58:28,320
Thanks, Jacob.

822
00:58:36,160 --> 00:58:38,840
I would've liked to have known
my grandchildren.

823
00:58:38,880 --> 00:58:41,360
Don't go away!
Don't leave us!

824
00:58:43,800 --> 00:58:46,120
Don't cry, Jacob.

825
00:58:46,160 --> 00:58:49,640
What is this?
"Uncle Tom's Cabin?"

826
00:58:50,200 --> 00:58:52,080
I know.

827
00:58:52,080 --> 00:58:56,200
I know what you think.
People make fun of me.

828
00:58:56,240 --> 00:58:58,760
Not just in the club...

829
00:58:58,800 --> 00:59:01,480
but in the street as well.
Everywhere.

830
00:59:04,120 --> 00:59:07,240
I'm aware that I'm ridiculous.

831
00:59:07,280 --> 00:59:10,760
And there's only one place
where no one is ridiculous.

832
00:59:11,760 --> 00:59:12,840
And I'm going there.

833
00:59:14,320 --> 00:59:16,360
Good-bye, Renato.

834
00:59:16,400 --> 00:59:18,000
Don't leave!

835
00:59:19,320 --> 00:59:23,920
I'm leaving you my stereo,
my red boots, and my wigs.

836
00:59:23,960 --> 00:59:26,040
But where are you going?

837
00:59:26,080 --> 00:59:27,680
To Foissy!

838
00:59:27,720 --> 00:59:31,520
Foissy? There's nothing
but a cemetery in Foissy.

839
00:59:31,600 --> 00:59:34,280
That's why
I'm taking the minimum.

840
00:59:35,600 --> 00:59:37,480
A toothbrush to the cemetery?

841
00:59:49,000 --> 00:59:52,320
-It's over, Jacob.
-I'm praying.

842
01:00:28,440 --> 01:00:31,560
You know,
my cemetery is in Lombardy.

843
01:00:31,600 --> 01:00:34,040
It's the prettiest in the world.

844
01:00:34,080 --> 01:00:37,200
There are trees.
The sky is blue.

845
01:00:37,240 --> 01:00:38,360
There are birds.

846
01:00:41,000 --> 01:00:44,040
Yours is for shit.

847
01:00:44,080 --> 01:00:47,720
It's true. In Foissy,
they bury the dead in shit.

848
01:00:51,120 --> 01:00:54,960
Forgive me for saying this,
but you've become an old hag.

849
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:58,440
It's true, you're worthless,
you're ridiculous.

850
01:00:58,480 --> 01:01:00,760
You make people laugh.

851
01:01:02,440 --> 01:01:07,000
But I'm with you.
Because you make me laugh.

852
01:01:08,040 --> 01:01:09,920
So you know
what I'm going to do?

853
01:01:12,160 --> 01:01:16,320
Leave everything behind and go
with you to the shit at Foissy.

854
01:01:16,360 --> 01:01:17,880
To laugh.

855
01:01:20,680 --> 01:01:23,880
Every time you're with her,
the same thing happens.

856
01:01:23,920 --> 01:01:26,560
In 20 years,
it's just the second time!

857
01:01:26,600 --> 01:01:30,120
Imagine having another child
at your age.

858
01:01:30,160 --> 01:01:34,000
You'd take care of the tiny tot
by yourself, my dear.

859
01:01:34,040 --> 01:01:36,480
I couldn't deal
with a second motherhood.

860
01:01:38,760 --> 01:01:40,800
What's so funny?

861
01:01:40,840 --> 01:01:44,040
I'm really ready
to strangle you.

862
01:02:08,160 --> 01:02:10,640
I'd like to talk to you.

863
01:02:13,280 --> 01:02:16,000
I know you're having problems.

864
01:02:18,080 --> 01:02:22,240
I know the press is still
interested in us, and so--

865
01:02:23,640 --> 01:02:25,600
I wanted to tell you that...

866
01:02:27,840 --> 01:02:29,920
the people we're going to--

867
01:02:29,960 --> 01:02:31,040
Wait!

868
01:02:37,960 --> 01:02:39,960
This meat is not fresh.

869
01:02:40,000 --> 01:02:41,320
I'll exchange it right away.

870
01:02:41,360 --> 01:02:45,040
No, leave it. I don't want more
of the same junk.

871
01:02:45,080 --> 01:02:49,320
It's shocking that a place like
this would serve rotten meat!

872
01:02:49,360 --> 01:02:52,440
I'll take it back.
What else can I do?

873
01:02:52,480 --> 01:02:56,040
I'll tell you what I'm going
to do. Write to Michelin.

874
01:02:56,080 --> 01:02:59,200
You'll have fewer stars
in the next guidebook.

875
01:02:59,240 --> 01:03:00,360
That's it.

876
01:03:02,680 --> 01:03:04,080
Well done, Simon.

877
01:03:05,280 --> 01:03:08,040
Now what about all the people
we're going to see?

878
01:03:08,080 --> 01:03:11,160
Nothing.
It's nothing important.

879
01:03:21,120 --> 01:03:25,240
Good, Jacob...very good.
A perfect butler.

880
01:03:32,760 --> 01:03:34,440
Haven't you forgotten
something?

881
01:03:37,560 --> 01:03:41,720
I can't wear shoes. I never
wear them. They make me fall!

882
01:03:41,760 --> 01:03:44,800
Go on. Go put your shoes on.

883
01:03:44,840 --> 01:03:47,120
And use your normal voice.
It's better.

884
01:03:47,160 --> 01:03:50,880
The little white master wanted
the voice of a real black male.

885
01:03:52,840 --> 01:03:54,440
Perfect, Dad.

886
01:03:54,480 --> 01:03:55,400
You think so?

887
01:03:56,920 --> 01:03:59,040
This suit reminds me
of my grandfather.

888
01:03:59,920 --> 01:04:01,600
He always dressed like this.

889
01:04:02,400 --> 01:04:05,000
He killed himself
when he was 30.

890
01:04:05,040 --> 01:04:06,680
Remember, Dad.

891
01:04:06,720 --> 01:04:08,560
As few gestures as possible.

892
01:04:08,600 --> 01:04:11,480
And don't walk around,
and don't talk too much.

893
01:04:11,520 --> 01:04:12,960
Just what's necessary.

894
01:04:13,040 --> 01:04:14,800
The minimum.

895
01:04:58,960 --> 01:05:00,200
What's wrong?

896
01:05:04,320 --> 01:05:06,320
I'm dressed appropriately,
aren't l?

897
01:05:09,480 --> 01:05:12,000
Nothing on my fingers.

898
01:05:12,040 --> 01:05:14,720
Nothing on my eyes or lips.

899
01:05:23,480 --> 01:05:24,680
And on your feet?

900
01:05:26,360 --> 01:05:29,560
I thought a little hint of color
wouldn't be out of place.

901
01:05:34,440 --> 01:05:36,520
Yes, you're right.

902
01:05:36,560 --> 01:05:40,040
Dressed like this
I am even more ridiculous.

903
01:05:40,080 --> 01:05:43,080
And I know
you're thinking that, too.

904
01:05:43,120 --> 01:05:44,680
Well...

905
01:05:46,440 --> 01:05:47,840
I'll leave.

906
01:05:50,880 --> 01:05:51,920
I'll go.

907
01:05:57,720 --> 01:06:00,520
I wanted so much to help you,
my little one.

908
01:06:09,280 --> 01:06:10,440
It'll pass.

909
01:06:44,360 --> 01:06:45,640
Who is it?

910
01:06:53,240 --> 01:06:54,720
My mother.

911
01:06:59,880 --> 01:07:01,960
Mr. Baldi's not here.

912
01:07:02,000 --> 01:07:02,920
Who's speaking?

913
01:07:04,400 --> 01:07:06,120
Is it you, Laurent?

914
01:07:08,400 --> 01:07:13,000
Laurent, I can imagine
what you think of me.

915
01:07:13,040 --> 01:07:16,560
After your father's visit, I
asked myself a lot of questions.

916
01:07:18,040 --> 01:07:21,640
You may think
it's a little late, but...

917
01:07:21,680 --> 01:07:24,560
Listen, Laurent,
your father's right.

918
01:07:24,600 --> 01:07:27,000
It'll be better
with a woman there.

919
01:07:27,040 --> 01:07:31,600
Since I'm already on the road...

920
01:07:31,640 --> 01:07:34,800
if you still want me...
I'll come.

921
01:07:37,720 --> 01:07:39,200
Come.

922
01:07:40,880 --> 01:07:43,800
Come?!
Have you gone crazy, Laurent?

923
01:07:43,840 --> 01:07:46,440
It'll be better if she's here.

924
01:07:46,480 --> 01:07:50,600
Do you know what he will do if
your mother sets foot in here?

925
01:07:50,640 --> 01:07:53,000
He said he wanted to help me.
He'll be good.

926
01:07:53,880 --> 01:07:56,680
Come on, relax.
Everything will be fine.

927
01:07:56,720 --> 01:07:59,080
Touch this. Squeeze it hard.

928
01:08:17,640 --> 01:08:20,600
We rented you for only one day,
but if all goes well...

929
01:08:20,640 --> 01:08:21,920
I'm willing to buy you...

930
01:08:23,080 --> 01:08:24,360
and get rid of my charm.

931
01:08:24,400 --> 01:08:26,160
In fact, I'll do it right now.

932
01:08:37,280 --> 01:08:39,000
You have your shoes on?
Go on.

933
01:09:02,480 --> 01:09:04,360
I'm honored. Please, come in.

934
01:09:05,800 --> 01:09:06,920
My father.

935
01:09:14,160 --> 01:09:14,920
My daughter.

936
01:09:14,960 --> 01:09:16,200
Nice to meet you.

937
01:09:17,520 --> 01:09:18,560
My husband.

938
01:09:19,560 --> 01:09:20,800
It's a great honor.

939
01:09:22,200 --> 01:09:24,120
My mother apologizes.
She'll be late.

940
01:09:24,160 --> 01:09:28,520
She had to take my brothers
and sisters to my grandparents'.

941
01:09:30,760 --> 01:09:33,880
Andrea told us that you have
a large family, Mr. Baldi.

942
01:09:33,920 --> 01:09:34,960
Quite large.

943
01:09:35,000 --> 01:09:37,440
How many brothers and sisters
does Laurent have?

944
01:09:40,320 --> 01:09:42,520
-Six.
-Six.

945
01:09:43,120 --> 01:09:45,360
People don't have children
anymore:

946
01:09:45,400 --> 01:09:48,880
Our movement is very worried
about this drop in births.

947
01:09:48,920 --> 01:09:53,520
I congratulate you. Your family
should be held up as an example.

948
01:09:55,200 --> 01:09:58,280
Have a seat, please.
One, two, three.

949
01:10:17,200 --> 01:10:18,640
This is Charrier's chauffeur.

950
01:10:18,680 --> 01:10:22,200
Just a second.
Charrier's chauffeur.

951
01:10:24,920 --> 01:10:26,920
The Charriers are
at "La Cage aux Folles."

952
01:10:26,960 --> 01:10:28,120
Are you sure?

953
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:31,240
I'm sure. I just left them
at the owner's place.

954
01:10:32,200 --> 01:10:34,080
Call Moreau in Toulon fast!

955
01:10:35,120 --> 01:10:37,960
Charrier with fags!
What a story!

956
01:10:38,000 --> 01:10:40,560
Did you have a good trip?

957
01:10:40,600 --> 01:10:45,160
Great.
Beautiful weather, good roads.

958
01:10:45,200 --> 01:10:48,280
We spent the night...

959
01:10:48,320 --> 01:10:51,280
near Lyon,
at my friend Bouchard's.

960
01:10:51,320 --> 01:10:54,080
He's someone
I met in the service.

961
01:10:54,120 --> 01:10:58,840
I met him again a few years
later in the hotel business.

962
01:10:58,880 --> 01:11:02,320
He had inherited...

963
01:11:02,360 --> 01:11:04,480
a large property
from his father

964
01:11:04,520 --> 01:11:08,520
and turned it
into a modern hotel.

965
01:11:08,560 --> 01:11:11,360
Comfortable. Yes, comfortable.
Very nice.

966
01:11:11,400 --> 01:11:13,120
Quite good. Quite good.

967
01:11:14,880 --> 01:11:17,640
It was a pleasant...stay.

968
01:11:25,640 --> 01:11:28,160
I like the severity
of this room.

969
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:33,360
Well, for my father...
this house...

970
01:11:33,400 --> 01:11:36,800
is a place more for work
and concentration...

971
01:11:36,840 --> 01:11:38,720
than a vacation house.

972
01:11:38,760 --> 01:11:40,400
A monastery.

973
01:11:42,800 --> 01:11:45,240
I captured the atmosphere
right away.

974
01:11:45,280 --> 01:11:48,760
I can always tell right away
who I'm dealing with.

975
01:11:51,600 --> 01:11:56,400
I'm pleased to say...
I feel good with a man like you.

976
01:11:56,440 --> 01:11:58,760
You've seduced my husband,
Mr. Baldi.

977
01:11:58,800 --> 01:12:02,760
I rarely hear him give
so many compliments.

978
01:12:05,400 --> 01:12:08,120
In fact, I must admit...

979
01:12:08,160 --> 01:12:10,080
that though
I'm a civil servant--

980
01:12:11,720 --> 01:12:16,160
Champagne, or do you prefer
something else?

981
01:12:17,560 --> 01:12:20,520
No, thank you.
Just some water, please.

982
01:12:20,560 --> 01:12:24,920
I never drink either, but today,
I'll make an exception.

983
01:12:28,720 --> 01:12:30,720
Watch what you're doing, idiot!

984
01:12:30,760 --> 01:12:33,600
Nothing serious.
Champagne brings luck.

985
01:12:33,680 --> 01:12:35,840
Go on, Jacob. We'll handle it.

986
01:12:40,600 --> 01:12:42,040
Can I help you?

987
01:12:42,080 --> 01:12:46,720
Jacob's a good fellow,
but he still has a lot to learn.

988
01:12:46,760 --> 01:12:50,480
Help is really a problem
these days.

989
01:12:50,520 --> 01:12:54,080
If I told you how many
chauffeurs I've had this year...

990
01:12:54,120 --> 01:12:58,280
You must have even more trouble
since you travel so much.

991
01:13:03,120 --> 01:13:04,120
Here I am.

992
01:13:06,360 --> 01:13:08,800
I'm here! Here's Mother!

993
01:13:12,600 --> 01:13:17,120
Please forgive me. I'm terribly
sorry, but the traffic--

994
01:13:17,160 --> 01:13:20,880
Every day it gets worse.
It's becoming impossible.

995
01:13:20,920 --> 01:13:23,240
Mr. Charrier,
thrilled to meet you!

996
01:13:26,880 --> 01:13:30,400
I've been dying to meet the
father of that naughty girl...

997
01:13:30,440 --> 01:13:31,840
who's stealing my baby.

998
01:13:33,640 --> 01:13:35,240
The naughty thing!

999
01:13:37,720 --> 01:13:42,480
Dear Madam, I'm just joking.
I already like the child.

1000
01:13:42,520 --> 01:13:45,040
What a sweet thing!

1001
01:13:45,080 --> 01:13:48,960
How about a kiss? How about
a kiss for your second mother?

1002
01:13:49,040 --> 01:13:53,040
Come here, darling.
I already love her.

1003
01:13:53,080 --> 01:13:55,000
She's adorable.

1004
01:13:55,040 --> 01:13:56,800
She's frightened, poor dear.

1005
01:13:56,840 --> 01:14:00,240
Come here.
Don't be afraid.

1006
01:14:00,280 --> 01:14:02,880
She's adorable.

1007
01:14:07,480 --> 01:14:08,880
Give me a cigarette.

1008
01:14:08,920 --> 01:14:11,840
Go warn your mother not to come.

1009
01:14:11,880 --> 01:14:13,160
Thanks.

1010
01:14:16,200 --> 01:14:18,480
Excuse me for a moment.

1011
01:14:18,520 --> 01:14:20,560
Where's the boy going?

1012
01:14:20,600 --> 01:14:22,440
Dinner is served.

1013
01:14:27,400 --> 01:14:31,400
-Jacob, what's come over you?
-Nothing. Nothing at all.

1014
01:14:32,760 --> 01:14:36,640
-Servants are such a problem.
-We were just saying that.

1015
01:14:36,680 --> 01:14:40,000
It's close to impossible
to get good help these days.

1016
01:14:40,080 --> 01:14:45,360
You can't imagine how many maids
have passed through here.

1017
01:14:45,400 --> 01:14:50,560
And one's as clumsy as the next.
Not mean, just inept.

1018
01:14:50,600 --> 01:14:55,160
I could name a dozen--
Roger, Marcel, Luciano...

1019
01:14:55,200 --> 01:14:58,040
Dinner.

1020
01:14:58,080 --> 01:15:00,000
No need to be so nasty.

1021
01:15:01,880 --> 01:15:05,080
Magnificent.
That Christ is splendid.

1022
01:15:05,120 --> 01:15:06,840
-Yes. My father.
-Pardon me?

1023
01:15:06,880 --> 01:15:08,720
My father, he restored it.

1024
01:15:08,760 --> 01:15:12,560
My father loved antiques.

1025
01:15:12,600 --> 01:15:16,800
Mr. Charrier on my right.
Renato on my left.

1026
01:15:16,840 --> 01:15:20,960
Mrs. Charrier there,
and the girl across from mama.

1027
01:15:21,000 --> 01:15:23,120
Please, sit down.

1028
01:15:26,760 --> 01:15:29,560
These plates are very unusual.

1029
01:15:30,840 --> 01:15:34,720
They're pictures of young men
playing together.

1030
01:15:34,760 --> 01:15:38,440
We have so many plates, I can't
really say which ones those are.

1031
01:15:38,480 --> 01:15:40,760
From the 16th century.

1032
01:15:40,800 --> 01:15:43,200
I think they are Greek figures.

1033
01:15:43,240 --> 01:15:47,040
Greeks on my plates?
How did they get there?

1034
01:15:47,120 --> 01:15:49,640
Would you like to see it?

1035
01:15:49,680 --> 01:15:52,120
I can't see without my glasses.

